## General Guidelines

1. **Always check `@api` first** before creating custom implementations
2. **Use proper cleanup** - Remove listeners/patches in plugin `stop()` method
3. **Follow plugin lifecycle** - Register APIs in `start()`, unregister in `stop()`
4. **Use ErrorBoundary** - APIs automatically wrap components, but be aware of error handling
5. **Check dependencies** - Some APIs require specific plugin dependencies
6. **Use TypeScript types** - All APIs are fully typed
7. **Read API documentation** - Each API file has JSDoc comments

---

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **DON'T**: Manually patch UI components
```typescript
// BAD
const MessageComponent = findByPropsLazy("message");
// Patch it manually...

// GOOD
import { MessageAccessories } from "@api";
MessageAccessories.addMessageAccessory("my-id", render);
```

❌ **DON'T**: Use localStorage for complex data
```typescript
// BAD
localStorage.setItem("data", JSON.stringify(complexObject));

// GOOD
import { DataStore } from "@api";
await DataStore.set("myPlugin:data", complexObject);
```

❌ **DON'T**: Directly access Discord settings
```typescript
// BAD
const settings = UserSettingsActionCreators.getCurrentValue();

// GOOD
import { UserSettings } from "@api";
const setting = UserSettings.getUserSetting("group", "name");
```

❌ **DON'T**: Create custom notification systems
```typescript
// BAD
const notification = new Notification("Title", { body: "Body" });

// GOOD
import { Notifications } from "@api";
Notifications.showNotification({ title: "Title", body: "Body" });
```

❌ **DON'T**: Forget to cleanup in stop()
```typescript
// BAD
export default definePlugin({
    start() {
        MessageEvents.addMessageClickListener(listener);
    }
    // No cleanup!
});

// GOOD
export default definePlugin({
    start() {
        MessageEvents.addMessageClickListener(listener);
    },
    stop() {
        MessageEvents.removeMessageClickListener(listener);
    }
});
```

